Section 2    Diabetes Mellitus - The Secret of
                        Prevention and Reversal
                             (part two)

                        By Dr. Boyce N. Berkel
           http://www.uniquenterprises.com/html/mt.htm

        Read about Dr. Boyce Berkel on our Meet the Team
        page; http://www.Life-Choices.com/team.html

----------
The Secret of Preventing and Reversing Diabetes is
presented in a  3-part series. In part one you got an
overview of the problem of diabetes, and the dynamics
that play a role in it's development. Last month in Part
two,  you found out the "secret" of preventing and
reversing diabetes. Today in part three, you will find out
how to manage the degenarative conditions associated
with diabetes such as - obesity and hypertension, vascular
diseases, diabetic retinopathy, diabetic neuropathy,
amyotrophic lateral sclerosis, and infections.


            OBESITY AND HYPERTENSION

Obesity and hypertension are considered together because of
their frequent association and common cause.  The common
denominator between obesity and hypertension is hyperinsulinism.

Hyperinsulinism disorganizes kidney function, and this causes
hypertension. The answer here is to stop the hyperinsulinism
by going on a 4 Day Diversified Rotation Diet.

A special treatment for hypertension is to first of all follow the
basic treatment program and add to this the magnetic treatment
of the kidneys. This will not only immediately help the kidneys
work better, but also has the effect of healing the kidneys from
the damage that has been done by the prolonged exposure to
hyperinsulinism.

Hyperinsulinism stimulates the liver to turn carbohydrates into
fats, leading to obesity. This explains why calorie restricted diets
sometimes don't work. The answer is to first of all stop the
hyperinsulinism by going on a 4 Day Diversified Rotation Diet
and then associate this with a calorie reduction diet.

Add to this the benefit of magnetic therapy. Magnets stimulate
the production of growth hormones. Growth hormone has as one
of its functions, the capacity to drop the fat from the fat cells.
Magnets can also be placed directly over the fatty areas. The time
for magnetic treatment is critical.  Growth hormone is only high
at night during sleep and therefore, the only appropriate time for
magnetic treatment of the fatty areas is during sleep.

                        VASCULAR DISEASES

Macrovascular diseases such as coronary artery disease, cerebral
artery disease or peripheral vascular disease require a negative
magnetic field treatment over an extended period of time. A
lifestyle of nightly treatment (all night) is preferred. It will take
several months to reduce atheromatous plaques and thus reduce
symptoms.

This magnetic heart treatment is suitable for any and all cardiac
complications such as skipped or irregular beats, angina, cardiac
failure, post-coronary occlusion or any demonstrated abnormality
of the heart. Mitral valve prolapse is a condition resulting from a
swollen mitral valve. This is classically due to maladaptive food
reactions. This is treated by the 4-Day Rotation Diet and the
application of the negative pole of a negative magnetic field
directly over the heart.

The classic reasons given for the development of atherosclerotic
plaques are: 1) elevated insulin, 2) elevated blood sugar,
3) hypetriglyceridemia, and 4) glycation (caramelization).

Atheromatous plaques are formed by the precipitation of
amino acids and minerals (mostly calcium). Amino acids
are soluble in an alkaline medium and form insoluble gels
in an acid medium. Calcium is soluble in an alkaline medium
and form insoluble crystal precipitates in an acid medium.
Atheromatous plaques are a combination of these amino
acid and mineral insoluble deposits.

The acid state is produced by maladaptive reactions to foods
and chemicals. The answer to these atheromatous producing
states is to rotate the foods and avoid the chemicals that are
evoking maladaptive reactions. Then treat the affected area
with a negative magnetic field. A negative magnetic field
normalizes the pH to its normal alkaline state. Over a period
of time, this alkalinization, resolves the atheromatous
plaques by causing the amino acids and the minerals to go
back into solution.

Microvascular disease consists of capillary basement
membrane thickening and accumulation of insoluble
precipitates within the microvascular nets. This microvascular
disease condition can develop in any organ including the skin.
The answer to microvascular disease is to stop the
maladaptive reaction to foods by a 4 Day Diversified Rotation
Diet. The treatment for these microvascular diseased areas is
to place a negative magnetic field directly over them.

                     DIABETIC RETINOPATHY
                ( Diabetic eye degeneration)

An assortment of degenerative eye conditions develop as a
complication of the diabetes mellitus disease process both
in the compensated and decompensated stages. These
degenerations include the retina (diabetic retinopathy),
cataracts, macular degeneration and glaucoma. Beyond the
basic treatment, the eyes need to be specifically treated with
magnetic therapy. Special precautions need to be taken if
glaucoma is present.

                    DIABETIC NEUROPATHY

Nerve deterioration may occur in any part of the body as a
complication of the diabetes mellitus disease process. The
arms, shoulders, neck, legs or feet may be involved. Pain is
the most common symptom in neuropathy. The most
common area for pain is in the feet. This is sometimes
described as a burning pain in the soles of the feet. The
placement of a negative magnetic field over the painful area
is the most successful treatment, being superior to the usual
nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory agents and even superior
to narcotics. Magnetic therapy will often relieve the pain
where none of these usual pain relieving agents is successful.

                        AMYOTROPHY

Amyotrophy consists of injured neurones which eventually
die. Muscles enervated by these dying neurones waste and
become nonfunctional. This is a painless muscle wasting
condition. Most often, this occurs first in the lower
extremities. When this condition occurs in the compensated
diabetes mellitus stage, before the diagnostic criteria of
clinically significant diabetes mellitus is present, it is given
the diagnostic name of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS).
When a person  has been diagnosed as having clinically
significant diabetes mellitus it is diagnosed as a complication
of diabetes mellitus with the name of diabetic amyotrophy.
The answer is, first of all to rotate your foods on a 4 Day
Diversified basis. It is also wise to take manganese and
arginine supplements. Although, reliance on supplementing
arginine and manganese without rotating the foods is not
going to achieve the optimum function of the urea cycle.

Diabetics in the decompensated stage characteristically have
hyperammonemia. A lesser number in the compensated stage
also have hyperammonemia.

Autopsy examinations of amyotrophy lateral sclerosis cases
has demonstrated the consistent presence of ammonia at the
site of the deteriorated neurones. Therefore, it is concluded
that the known neuro-toxic qualities of ammonia is the cause
of amyotrophy whether this is in amyotrophic lateral
sclerosis or in classically diagnosed diabetic amyotrophy.

Obviously, the therapeutic goal is to first of all, stop this
hyperammonemia so as to stop the killing of neurones. The
second goal is to reverse the state of the neurones that have
been injured but are not yet dead. By reversing the injured
state of neurones that are not yet dead there can be some
degree of recovery and there also can be the prevention of
the progression of the disease process. Therefore, it pays
to treat the spine with a negative magnetic field.

                         INFECTIONS

The skin of diabetics is not healthy and quite commonly,
especially in the feet, ulcers will develop. These have a mixed
type of bacterial and fungal infections. This can be
sufficiently disordering as to produce gangrene. Beyond the
basic treatment as described above, the local area should be
treated with a negative magnetic field. This treatment works
surprisingly well.

The negative magnetic field has an antibiotic effect against
any type of bacterial, any type of fungus and any type of virus.
Negative magnetic field therapy requires two weeks
minimum of 24-hour a day exposure to handle a local
infection.

