           BROWN RICE and ADUKI BEAN SALAD

                     by Andrea Lemieux, RNCP

      Read about Andrea Lemieux on our Meet the Team page;
              http://www.Life-Choices.com/team.html

-----
This recipe is perfect to take on a picnic or to bring to a pot
luck dinner. The rice and beans make a complete protein and
it is delicious served hot or cold.

Serves 4
1 1/4 cups water
3/4 cups brown basmati rice
1/4 teaspoon Celtic sea salt (gray salt)
1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil
1 tablespoon grated fresh ginger
2 cloves garlic, minced
1/3 cup finely chopped carrot
1/3 cup finely chopped celery
1/3 cup finely chopped red bell pepper
1 cup cooked aduki beans
1/2 cup sliced green onions
2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro (or parsley)

Dressing:
1 tablespoon brown rice vinegar
1 tablespoon brown rice syrup
2 tablespoons tamari
1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil
1 tablespoon sesame seeds, lightly toasted
1 tablespoon water

. Bring water to a boil. Add rice and salt, return to a boil,
    then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or
    until rice is completely cooked.
. Heat oil. Add garlic and ginger and saut#233# for one minute.
    Add vegetables and saute for 4 to 5 minutes. Add to the
    cooked rice.
.Combine cooked aduki beans with green onions and cilantro
    and add to the rice and vegetables.

Dressing:
.Whisk all ingredients together in a small bowl until thoroughly
    blended. Add to the rice and vegetables and toss thoroughly.

